# Trivy CVE allowlist for ghcr.io/ray-manaloto/dotfiles-devcontainer.
#
# Format: one CVE-XXXX-NNNNN per line. Lines starting with `#` are
# comments. Trivy reads this file from the image-scan working directory
# (the repo root in our CI workflow).
#
# When the Trivy step in `.github/workflows/ci.yml` is configured with
# `exit-code: "0"`, this file is advisory — SARIF still uploads to
# GitHub code scanning. When that step is flipped to `exit-code: "1"`
# (so the scan gates PRs on regressions), entries below suppress
# specific accepted-risk CVEs from the gate. The flip is tracked at
# https://github.com/ray-manaloto/dotfiles/issues/92 .
#
# Each entry MUST include a comment line above documenting:
#   - Why the CVE is accepted (upstream wontfix? not exploitable in
#     our usage? mitigated by isolation?).
#   - When to re-evaluate (e.g., "drop when ubuntu:26.05 lands").
